description:
I wish I had a magic formula but I also want to be transparent about how I got high paying jobs  as a full time student.
Here‚Äôs my advice: 

-work in different areas, develop your skills 
- as a beginner, focus on the EXPERIENCE you will gain, not money. The money will come later. 
-Take initiatives, make your name
known. TALK TO EVERYONE
-Make connections, they will bring you
better opportunities! 
-Apply to positions that align 
with your goals. Keep applying. 
(It took me like 8 rejected applications & 6 failed interviews before I found the $17/hr job) 
- Negotiate. Be humble but know your worth. 

For the people asking how I got my current jobs‚Ä¶.

I got them by applying directly on the university‚Äôs website. (I got rejected from multiple positions at the university before I got these) here‚Äôs what I needed for those positions:

Research assistant- bilingual, knowledge of sexual health & research, design & social media skills, quantitative data analysis experience, team player, etc. 
Student Director- leadership experience, workshop and project facilitation, event planning, proficiency with tech platforms, relationship development with diverse groups, etc. 

I also held leadership positions when I was in community college which got me even more experience + connections ü´∂üèº 

THAT‚ÄôS the tea üçµ
